The paper discusses location privacy protection mechanisms (LPPMs) for location-based services (LBSs), which are related to cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a framework for dynamically configuring LPPMs, which involves data management (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper evaluates the framework on real-life mobility datasets, which involves data analysis (cs.SI) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) aspects. Finally, the paper discusses privacy and utility objectives, which are related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) research.
